javax.jaxtx.model.btp
Interface Cohesion

All Superinterfaces:
UserTransaction
public interface Cohesion
extends UserTransaction

A Cohesion extension of the basic UserTransaction. The Cohesion and Atom implementations may co-exist within the same address space.

prepare_inferiors

public StatusItem[] prepare_inferiors(java.lang.String[] participantIds,
                                      Qualifier[] qualifiers)
                               throws InvalidTransactionException,
                                      WrongStateException,
                                      HazardException,
                                      MixedException,
                                      InvalidParticipantException,
                                      TransactionCancelledException,
                                      NoTransactionException,
                                      SystemException
Prepare the transaction and have it call prepare on the set of inferiors specified. The cohesion may be prepared any number of times during its lifetime, although a single participant can only be prepared once.
Parameters:
String[] - participantIds The list of inferiors that are to be prepared.
Qualifier[] - qualifiers Any additional qualifiers that may affect the prepare.
Returns:
a status value for each inferior.
Throws:
InvalidTransactionException - Thrown if the transaction identity is invalid.
WrongStateException - Thrown if the transaction is in a state that does not allow it to issue prepare.
HazardException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a hazard heuristic.
MixedException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a mixed heuristic.
InvalidParticipantException - Thrown if the inferiors list is invalid.
TransactionCancelledException - Thrown if all inferiors cancel during prepare.
NoTransactionException - Thrown if there is no transaction associated with the invoking thread.
SystemException - Thrown in the event of a general fault.

String[] - participantIds The list of inferiors that are to be cancelled.
Qualifier[] - qualifiers Any additional qualifiers that may affect the cancel.
Returns:
a status value for each inferior.
Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the transaction is in a state that does not allow it to issue cancel.
InvalidTransactionException - Thrown if the transaction identity is invalid.
HazardException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a hazard heuristic.
MixedException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a mixed heuristic.
InvalidParticipantException - Thrown if the inferior list is invalid.
NoTransactionException - Thrown if there is no transaction associated with the invoking thread.
TransactionConfirmedException - Thrown if all inferiors confirm during cancel.
SystemException - Thrown in the event of a general fault.

Confirm the transaction and have it call confirm on the set of inferiors specified. Once confirmed, the cohesion is terminated.
Parameters:
Qualifier[] - qualifiers Any additional qualifiers that may affect the confirm.
Returns:
a status value for each inferior or null if they all confirmed.
Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the transaction is in a state that does not allow it to issue confirm.
InvalidTransactionException - Thrown if the transaction identity is invalid.
HazardException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a hazard heuristic.
MixedException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a mixed heuristic.
NoTransactionException - Thrown if there is no transaction associated with the invoking thread.
TransactionCancelledException - Thrown if all inferiors cancel during confirm.
SystemException - Thrown in the event of a general fault.

Cancel the transaction and have it call confirm on the set of inferiors specified. Once cancelled in this manner, the cohesion is terminated.
Parameters:
Qualifier[] - qualifiers Any additional qualifiers that may affect the confirm.
Returns:
a status value for each inferior or null if they all cancelled.
Throws:
WrongStateException - Thrown if the transaction is in a state that does not allow it to issue cancel.
InvalidTransactionException - Thrown if the transaction identity is invalid.
HazardException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a hazard heuristic.
MixedException - Thrown if the inferiors generate a mixed heuristic.
NoTransactionException - Thrown if there is no transaction associated with the invoking thread.
TransactionConfirmedException - Thrown if all inferiors confirm during cancel.
SystemException - Thrown in the event of a general fault.
